<br>
Max = ((Str + Skill + Level)/100)* damage<br>
<br>
If you log all the hits you deliver, and graph them over time, you'll notice there are 3 spikes in that graph.  Your maximum, minimum, and your mode (&quot;magic number&quot;).  Str only affects your max, it does not seem to change your minimum (which is (level -25)/3), or your magic number (2* damage + (level-25)/3 ).<br>
<br>
So, not only is your str factored into your hits 10% of the time or less (depending upon who you ask), it is only one third of what goes into that max damage formula.  This is why people say strength is worthless.  It does raise your atk, but an earliar poster summed that up best:<br>
<br>
&quot;Attack = Composit number made up of your chance to hit and your Damage potential&quot;<br>
<br>
Basically, when your strength goes up, your max damage goes up.  Max damage is part of what goes into your atk.  Strength does not affect chance to hit at all.<br>
<br>
All this comes from Romidar's FAQ, which is based off the old parses from the PoN board if I remember right.  While it is dated to some extent, I dont think that the core rules of the game have changed enough to throw that data out the window. <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ukrazmos.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Krazmos</A> at: 2/5/02 5:03:41 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2F2F4F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/ushelrabbi.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Shelrabbi</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are Superior</span><br>  Posts: 86<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/6/02 6:10:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub14.ezboard.com/fthesteelwarriorthearena.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1084.topic&index=22>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: STR is worthless?</span><hr size=1> Thanks, that's the post I was talking about. <p>Shelrabbi Hassida<BR>
